California Department of Public Health, Healthcare-Associated Infections Program, Health Care Personnel Influenza Vaccination
Reported County

Facility_ID is the primary key used to track facility information for all facilities stored in the Electronic Licensing Management System (ELMS) for CDPH Center for Health Care Quality, Licensing and Certification Program.

Facility name for facilities reporting to National Healthcare Safety Network (NHSN) healthcare personnel influenza vaccination data for the 2023-24 influenza season, specifically October 1, 2023, through March 31, 2024 for California General Acute Care Hospitals reporting.

HAI Program designation for hospital types. These include major teaching, community (<125 beds, 125-250 beds, and >250 beds), pediatric, critical access, long-term acute care (LTAC), and free-standing rehabilitation hospitals.

Total number of Health Care Personnel (HCP) vaccinated. HCP include all paid (employee) and unpaid (licensed independent practitioners, other contract personnel and adult students/trainees and volunteers) persons working in health care settings and have the potential to transmit influenza to and from other HCP and patients.

In 2023-24, hospitals should have achieved at least 90% (Healthy People 2020 goal) HCP vaccination coverage. Did hospital achieve at least 90% HCP vaccination coverage in 2023-24?  Yes or No.
“Non-reporter” indicates if hospital did not report data (all data fields are blank); "Reported combined data" indicates when hospital reports consolidated data with another hospital.
